    "decision_handoff_body": "\n# Decision summary\n\nBitcoin reaching $76,000 at least once during Apr 13-19 ET remains a high-probability outcome, but post-synthesis review does not justify a confident edge versus the market. The best synthesis view is that this is still likely because the contract only requires a Binance BTC/USDT 1-minute high and BTC was already trading in the upper-$75k area, but the remaining uncertainty is concentrated in path/timing and Binance-specific execution rather than broad directional thesis.\n\n## Why this may matter now\n\nMarket implied probability is 0.89. My synthesized range is 0.85 to 0.91. That reads as marginal-to-unclear edge, not a strong actionable divergence. The only plausible mispricing is that the market may be a touch too confident or too cautious about the remaining venue-specific path risk, but the difference is small and fragile.\n\n## Shift versus swarm baseline\n\nThe provisional swarm center was about 0.88, and my final range is centered very close to that baseline. I did not move materially because the synthesis-stage truth-finding supported the core swarm view: BTC remained near the barrier and the contract mechanics were permissive. I compressed the range slightly toward the market rather than endorsing the more bullish 0.92-0.93 lane estimates because independent verification still did not show the actual qualifying print.\n\n## Edge verification status\n\nIndependent verification quality is medium. I independently checked current Binance BTCUSDT state and confirmed BTC was still near the threshold, with last price around 75838 and 24h high around 75850 at synthesis time, still below 76000. That verification supports the high-probability framing but does not strongly verify any edge versus market, because it confirms proximity rather than completion. The main unverified point is the actual qualifying Binance 1-minute high >= 76000.\n\n## Compression toward market\n\nYes. Some lanes wanted to sit clearly above market because barrier proximity plus remaining time looked very favorable. I compressed toward market because the extra verification pass could confirm only that BTC was still close, not that the threshold had printed, and because the remaining uncertainty in these contracts is exactly the short-horizon path/venue detail that markets near 90% can still underestimate or overestimate by a few points.\n\n## Timing and catalyst posture\n\nThe next meaningful checkpoint is simply whether Binance prints a qualifying 76000+ 1-minute high. There is no obvious single scheduled catalyst that matters more than ordinary crypto volatility. The edge, if any, is more likely to decay than widen as time passes without a touch, because near-threshold failure becomes more informative in a short window.\n\n## Key blockers\n\nThere are no major research blockers, but there are operational blockers to high confidence: no verified qualifying print yet, and the market resolves on Binance-specific mechanics rather than generic spot. That argues for caution, not for broad uncertainty about the direction.\n\n## Best countercase\n\nThe strongest countercase, best represented by variant-view and partly by risk-manager, is that markets around 89% can still be too confident in a near-threshold setup when the event has not yet happened and settlement depends on one named venue's exact 1-minute high. A simple stall or reversal can still kill the trade.\n\n## What would change the view\n\nA direct verified Binance 1-minute high at or above 76000 would effectively collapse the uncertainty toward Yes. A meaningful reversal away from the barrier, especially back below 75k and persisting, would move the estimate down materially. Clean evidence that Binance was repeatedly failing while other venues tested the level would also make the market look too high.\n\n## Recommended next action\n\nRequest decision-maker review if action is still needed, but frame it as a near-market, modest-confidence synthesis rather than a strong edge call. If operating live, wait for the next Binance checkpoint rather than doing broader additional research.\n\n## Verification impact\n\nYes, synthesis-stage external verification was used. It materially confirmed the swarm's core premise that BTC was still very close to the barrier, but it did not confirm the event itself. Cross-lane comparison also exposed that some bullish lanes were leaning more on heuristic proximity than on direct settlement-venue completion, which justified slight compression toward the market rather than following the highest estimates.\n",
